Scripts and data driven maps for the article “Revisiting the Papez circuit using brain lesions and the structural and functional connectome”, by Ovando-Tellez, Kappel et al.

Data driven maps were obtained as follows: To identify functional and structural networks specifically associated with memory impairments, lesion maps from individuals with amnesia (n = 53) were compared with control stroke lesions without memory deficits (n = 490). For both functional (LNM-derived) and structural (disconnectome-derived) maps, voxel-wise group comparisons were conducted using two-sample t-test implemented in the Permutation Analysis of Linear Models (PALM) toolbox (https://fsl.fmrib.ox.ac.uk/fsl/fslwiki/PALM). All analyses were performed at the whole-brain level, with family-wise error (FWE) correction applied to control for multiple comparisons. Statistical significance was set at p < .05 (FWE-corrected). These analyses yielded data-driven functional and structural networks associated with memory impairment.

GM and WM mask for the classical Papez circuit are also provided. 
